      "role": "user",
      "content": "so you're saying the moral part is settled and the only real issue is the logistics? that basically makes the opposition's stance look like they're just making excuses to avoid doing the right thing. if the goal is to meet that moral baseline, isn't any argument that opposes universal coverage inherently failing that standard?",
