      "content": "It is an oversimplification to say the opposition's stance is merely an excuse, as their arguments are rooted in deeply held beliefs about economic freedom and individual responsibility. However, from a rights-based perspective, any system that systematically denies necessary care based on wealth fails the moral standard set by international declarations. The logistical challenges, while real, are not a defense against the moral obligation to ensure basic human dignity through healthcare access.",
